archive / f10-immunity-challenge Aunder 10/25/2024 12:53 PM # F10: SECRET LOVER 12:57 PM Here's how this will work! In a moment a public challenge chat will open up to all of the players and their loved ones. This is the ONLY place the challenge will be discussed publicly in the game. No tribe chat, no 1on1s, no vcs. You can of course discuss with your loved ones in your confessional. In this chat your goal is discover as many peoples loved ones as possible while hiding who yours is... mostly. 1:01 PM You want 5 of your other cast mates to guess who your loved one is correctly while the other 4 you do not. Here is how scoring will work: For every fellow cast mates loved one you guess correctly, you will gain 1 point The following are the point values you will obtain for each number of people correctly guessing your loved one: 0: 0 points 1: 1 point 2: 3 points 3: 5 points 4: 7 points 5: 10 points 6: 7 points 7: 5 points 8: 3 points 9: 1 point 1:02 PM The tiebreaker will come down to whoever got closest to 5 people guessing their loved one! 1:02 PM Say whatever you must to convince people one way or another, but just remember that all info is for everyone to see! Good luck :) KawaiiQuack 10/25/2024 7:08 PM @snazztastic human beings challenge 7:08 PM !!! archive / f11-immunity-challenge KawaiiQuack 10/22/2024 7:20 PM @snazztastic human beings hello again 7:20 PM Welcome to you're next challenge! 7:21 PM Nah I am kidding, no point in being silly Please go to #mail (again) and stop talking 7:21 PM You have all made the merge! Pilot 10/23/2024 4:01 PM Hello! 4:01 PM Welcome to 4:01 PM # F11 - AMONG US CHALLENGE 4:01 PM 4:02 PM Here's how it works! We're going to simulate 5 separate games of among us at once . And each game will have 2 impostors, randomly chosen, with identities only known to each other. Meaning that all of you (with one exception) will be the impostor in exactly 1 game, and crewmate in the other 4. (1 person will be a crewmate in all 5 games) This challenge will take place over 2 phases, each 12 hours long. (edited) 4:03 PM Each phase you will perform an action in each of the 5 games, depending on whether you are a crewmate or an impostor in that game! 4:04 PM PHASE 1 Crewmate Submit a vote for someone who they believe is the impostor. Choose a location to guard: The options include: Electrical, Reactor, Communications, Med-Bay, and Navigation. Impostor Select a player you would like to kill! They will not be able to participate in phase 2 Submit a vote for someone to be eliminated 4:05 PM Only vote counts, and who is killed will be revealed publicly for each game. The players who are killed along with the player who receive the most votes will not be allowed to participate in phase two for those games. (edited) 4:06 PM PHASE 2 Crewmate Submit a vote for someone who they believe is the impostor. Impostor Choose one location to sabotage! (same options as crewmate to guard) Select a player you would like to kill! Submit a vote for someone who you would like to see eliminated. (edited) 4:08 PM And the end of phase 2: 1. The votes will be revealed, and the person voted out is eliminated from the game 2. If the impostor has not been voted out, they will try to sabotage on of the locations. The sabotage will succeed if no crewmates are guarding the area. 3. If the impostor is still alive, their final kill goes through. (edited) 4:09 PM Points will then be tallied up and annouced 4:09 PM Points are given out as follows for each phase for each game (edited) 4:10 PM Phase 1: Crewmate receives 2 points if they vote for the impostor Crewmate receives 5 points if they are not killed/voted out Impostor receives 4 points if they are not voted out (edited) 4:13 PM Phase 2: Crewmate receives 3 points if they vote for the impostor Crewmate receives 7 points if they are not killed/voted out Impostor receives 6 points if they are not voted out (edited) 4:18 PM After Phase 2: If 2 impostors are alive, both receive 20 points. If 0 impostors are alive, all living crewmates receive 12 points If 1 impostor is alive living crewmates receive 5 points If the sabotage took place successfully, the living impostor(s) receive 30 points (edited) 4:19 PM As an example, I may receive this in my submissions as my assignment: Game 1: Crewmate Game 2: Crewmate Game 3: Impostor with Austin Game 4: Crewmate Game 5: Crewmate My phase one submissions could then look like Game 1: Arvid, Electrical Game 2: Austin, Med-Bay Game 3: Vote: Arvid Kill: Muski Game 4: Quack, Reactor Game 5: Cwis, Reactor And assuming I survive every game, my phase two submission could look like Game 1: Cwis Game 2: Cwis Game 3: Vote Cwis Kill: Quack Sabotage: Electrical Game 4: Austin Game 5: Arvid (edited) 4:20 PM The 2 players who receive the most points will win immunity! Phase 1 starts now, with a deadline at 10/24/2024 7:00 AM Pilot 10/23/2024 7:03 PM @Kireina 7:03 PM You'll be sent your assignments shortly! Pilot 10/23/2024 7:17 PM You may also discuss this challenge as much as you'd like with your tribemates! Pilot The 2 players who receive the most points will win immunity! Phase 1 starts now, with a deadline at 10/24/2024 7:00 AM Pilot 10/23/2024 10:59 PM @Kireina REMINDER PHASE 1 ACTIONS DUE IN 8 HOURS (edited) 11:00 PM You must complete phase 1 to be elligible for phase 2 Pilot 10/24/2024 7:22 AM Here are the round 1 results! 1 7:25 AM Meaning that: Nate, Willow, and Brett die in Game 1 IzzyB, Nate, and Cinnamon die in Game 2 LN, Brett, and Nate die in Game 3 Cinnamon, Dreya, and Pichu die in Game 4 Dreya, Nate, and IzzyB die in Game 5 7:26 AM Round 2 submissions due at 10/24/2024 7:00 PM ! 7:26 AM submit for only the games where you are alive still! Pilot 10/24/2024 6:59 PM Alright @snazztastic human beings Let's get to those results! 1 7:00 PM Starting with the kills and votes from round 2 7:01 PM 1 7:01 PM Thrilling! 7:01 PM Onto how the points actually shake up 7:01 PM In 11th place 7:02 PM Nate, with 28 points 7:02 PM In 10th place 7:02 PM Brett, with 44 points 7:02 PM In 9th place 7:02 PM Dreya, with 54 points 1 7:02 PM In 8th place 7:03 PM Cinnamon, with 72 points 7:03 PM In 7th place 7:03 PM IzzyB, with 82 points 7:03 PM In 6th place 7:03 PM Willow, with 88 points 7:04 PM In 5th place 7:04 PM Ln with 92 points 7:04 PM Onto our top 4 7:04 PM with a reminder that the top 2 scorers will both be immune 7:04 PM In 4th place (edited) 7:04 PM Tyler with 96 points 7:05 PM Meaning that our top 3 is Pichu, Alba, and Pigeon 7:05 PM And guess what? We have a tie 1 7:06 PM With 2 of those 3 receiving the highest possible score for this challenge 1 7:06 PM In 3rd place with a score of 104 7:06 PM Pichu! 7:07 PM Meaning with perfect scores of 176 @Alba and @2nd-Pigeon win immunity! 2 7:09 PM Exported 60 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f12-immunity-challenge KawaiiQuack 10/20/2024 6:29 PM Hello gamers For this challenge, we will be doing a Quack classic. Three Monkeys ! So here is how it works: You will need to get into two groups of three. This means one person from @Jax has to sit out, wile one person from @Ilana will have to be a part of both groups. There are three roles. First Monkey: You will be given Google Sheet art. On vc, you must describe the piece to the Second Monkey. Second Monkey: You must transcribe what is being told to you on vc to the Third Monkey over text. You are not allowed to speak to the First Monkey, you must be muted. Third Monkey: You will be given a blank canvas, and are tasked with using the directions from the Second Monkey to try to accurately recreate the art piece. 6:32 PM Your time starts when the Canvas is sent, and ends when you send a link of the completed work and a screenshot of said work. You must use the palette given on the second tab of the sheet. Failure to use the right colors will result in those cells being marked wrong, so be careful! Every incorrectly colored cell will be a five second penalty, meaning if you take 30 minutes but make 10 mistakes, your final time will be 30:50. The tribe with the faster combined time will win immunity! Please note, there are two artworks, one per group. Please ping me with who is doing what, and which group they are apart of (1 or 2). 6:37 PM And one more thing. There is a twist this round. Once again, both tribes are going to tribal, both sets of votes will be read, and the results of this challenge will not be revealed until after. However, the player voted out of the winning tribe will not have immunity at the next cycle. I think that is everything, if you have any questions, please ask! KawaiiQuack 10/20/2024 7:16 PM @snazztastic human beings welcome 7:16 PM Peep the challenge 7:16 PM Peep the twist 7:21 PM Please form your groups as soon as possible! Pilot 10/20/2024 7:25 PM Also, Jax you may not sit out the same person back to back, so @5th-Cinnamon must play 3 KawaiiQuack Your time starts when the Canvas is sent, and ends when you send a link of the completed work and a screenshot of said work. You must use the palette given on the second tab of the sheet. Failure to use the right colors will result in those cells being marked wrong, so be careful! Every incorrectly colored cell will be a five second penalty, meaning if you take 30 minutes but make 10 mistakes, your final time will be 30:50. The tribe with the faster combined time will win immunity! Please note, there are two artworks, one per group. Please ping me with who is doing what, and which group they are apart of (1 or 2). KawaiiQuack 10/21/2024 1:24 AM Unfortunate news Does not change anything for those that already ran it, but the penalty is actually 30 seconds and not 5. Sorry about that! KawaiiQuack 10/21/2024 4:44 PM Hey y'all! Due to some scheduling issues, we're giving an extension to this challenge. Since results are not being revealed tonight anyways, tribal channels will be open at the standard time. So functionally, nothing is changing, but feel free to get this challenge done at your own pace! KawaiiQuack 10/22/2024 7:09 PM @snazztastic human beings @All Updates What's up 2 7:09 PM Time for some results! 7:09 PM I will be snappy I promise 7:10 PM This was our first artwork. 7:10 PM For Jax... we had Tyler, Cinnamon and Pigeon. 7:11 PM All white cells were incorrect 7:11 PM The colored cells are what was correct 7:11 PM Lots of problems! 7:12 PM 327 mistakes 48:58 raw 2:43:30 penalty 3:32:28 total These are the stats 5 7:12 PM Alba, Izzy B, and Pichu did this one for Ilana 7:12 PM This was their success! 7:13 PM 38 mistakes 38:19 raw 19:00 penalty 57:19 total And these are their stats 7:13 PM Ilana takes a commanding lead 7:13 PM This was the second artwork 7:13 PM LN, Willow, and Keira completed this one 7:14 PM And this is what was correct 2 1 7:14 PM 429 mistakes 17:16 raw 3:34:30 penalty 3:51:46 total Stats 1 7:15 PM 7:24:14 is Jax's total time 1 7:15 PM It would take a colossal choke for Ilana to lose this 2 7:15 PM So... did they? 7:15 PM As you can see, they did not! 2 7:15 PM Nearly perfect! 7:16 PM I gotta say, I'm impressed 7:16 PM Truly 7:16 PM 4 mistakes 45:29 raw 2:00 penalty 47:29 total Stats 7:16 PM 1:44:48 is Ilana's total 7:16 PM Meaning... @Ilana wins their first immunity! 1 7:16 PM And now... #mail Exported 38 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f13-immunity-challenge Dicy 10/18/2024 6:45 PM Final 13 Challenge: Pictionary Framework Today you will be partnering up with-in your tribes to complete a Framework Puzzle, But there's a twist! That twist being you will not have any scrambled words to guide you! Instead of the standard scrambled up words you will be using drawings and a letter bank to solve the words used for the puzzle! In your pair, you need to assign two roles: a "Drawer" and a "Solver" . The goal is to solve a Framework-like puzzle! Here’s how it works: Role Assignment: Once you partnered up and have your roles assigned, please ping us in your tribe chat with the list of pairs and roles! Drawer Responsibilities: The Drawer will run the command ?13-Pictionary-Framework , which will give them ten survivor based words they must illustrate (on their own, no tracing or anything similar) without using any numbers, letters, or words. They will have 15 minutes to complete their drawings. If they take longer than this time limit, their team will be disqualified. (DQ penalty explained in scoring) Solver Responsibilities: Once the Drawer submits all ten drawings, Production will notify the solver. Once the solver is ready, the drawings will be handed over to the Solver. The Solver must then deduce the ten words from the drawings and integrate them into a Framework puzzle. Scoring: The scoring for this challenge will be based on the number of correct answers in the puzzle. In case of a tie, the time taken from when the Solver requests the drawings to the moment the completed puzzle is submitted will serve as the tiebreaker. DQ's For going over the drawing time or A none drawer entering the command will be 1.5x the overall worst time. 6:45 PM 6:45 PM For anyone who is not familiar with a Framework puzzle in general here is an example of a standard Framework puzzle (however you will not get the scrambled words section) 6:45 PM 6:46 PM If you have any questions please ping me! Pilot 10/18/2024 7:27 PM Jax you're sitting someone out btw! Dicy 10/18/2024 8:09 PM Small little note: as a drawer if you are coming up on the 15 time limit you can choose to submit the drawings you have and not give your solver all ten to avoid a DQ. However the solver will only get those done to solve the framework Dicy 10/19/2024 7:01 PM @All Updates @snazztastic human beings I HAVE SOME RESULTS 7:01 PM to start with good news, it didn't end up going to tie breaker! 7:02 PM let us kick things off with what the ten words were to start with 7:02 PM the list of words used for this challenge are: 1.) Fire Making 2.) Final Three 3.) Under the Radar 4.) Buff 5.) Jeff Probst 6.) Rocks 7.) Water Well 8.) Tribal Council 9.) Survivor Auction 10.) Idol 7:03 PM to save time, I will jump right to overall scores and then post a little chart breaking it down after 7:04 PM Winning immunity with a score of 20/30 compared to 10/30...... 7:04 PM @Jax Congrats you have the night off! 7:04 PM meaning @Ilana we will be seeing you at tribal council 7:05 PM as for the induvial pairs scores: 1 7:06 PM (I just realized i flipped those colors on the chart oops) Exported 17 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f14-immunity-challenge Armuski 10/16/2024 7:26 PM @snazztastic human beings @All Updates 7:27 PM Woah 7:27 PM We back baby 7:27 PM Last time I was here 7:27 PM I announced a swap 7:27 PM How funny was that 7:27 PM You probably didnt expect this but 7:27 PM DROP 7:27 PM Nothing? 7:27 PM Sorry for the lies. 7:28 PM But you know what they say 7:28 PM All is fair in love and ORGs 7:28 PM Speaking of, welcome to your next immunity challenge! 7:28 PM F14: All is fair Welcome to your second swap challenge! I hope you've all had time to settle into your tribes. This challenge is a rather simple one. You will be faced with a rotating jigsaw, and that's it! Of course that's not all there is to it. Everyone on each tribe will be doing the puzzle, and the time with the fastest average time wins immunity! How does one stop the other tribe from winning immunity then? Well, with WAR CARDS . These war cards are buffs and debuffs that can be played on your opponent! The 4 war cards are as follows: Doubles time Triples time Halves time Time doesnt count By playing these on your opponent, their time will be altered! If Dicy gets a time of 3:00, but has a triples time card on him, his time becomes 9:00. If Quack were to have a time of 0:30, and the opponents play a "time doesnt count" card, his time won't count towards the average! You pick who to play the cards on as a tribe and there is only one copy of each card per tribe . EVERY CARD NEEDS TO BE PLAYED ONCE The command to get the puzzle is "?f14-love" Make sure to /stopwatch beforehand The tribe that has the fastest time will win immunity and a surefire way to get to F14 7:29 PM If you have any questions, ping prod, I will be asleep :] Armuski F14: All is fair Welcome to your second swap challenge! I hope you've all had time to settle into your tribes. This challenge is a rather simple one. You will be faced with a rotating jigsaw, and that's it! Of course that's not all there is to it. These war cards are buffs and debuffs that can be played on your opponent! The 4 war cards are as follows: Doubles time Triples time Halves time Time doesnt count By playing these on your opponent, their time will be altered! If Dicy gets a time of 3:00, but has a triples time card on him, his time becomes 9:00. You pick who to play the cards on as a tribe and there is only one copy of each card per tribe . EVERY CARD NEEDS TO BE PLAYED ONCE The command to get the puzzle is "?f14-love" Make sure to /stopwatch beforehand The tribe that has the fastest time will win immunity and a surefire way to get to F14 Armuski 10/16/2024 7:30 PM If it wasnt clear, the war cards are played as a tribe in your tribes subs channel Armuski 10/16/2024 7:45 PM Please only out your FINAL SUBMISSION in the subs channel. All discussion should be held in tribe chat 7:48 PM You may do the challenge before dealing out war cards Armuski 10/17/2024 10:11 AM Reminder to use the stopwatch command! Armuski used /stopwatch start General Purpose ORG bot BOT 10/17/2024 10:11 AM Stopwatch Started! Note: stopwatch will stop after 1 day. Armuski used /stopwatch stop General Purpose ORG bot BOT 10/17/2024 10:11 AM Stopwatch stopped Time Elapsed 0:00:03.143000 Start Time 10:11:51 AM End Time 10:11:54 AM Timestamps are automatically corrected to your local timezone Armuski 10/17/2024 7:02 PM Grading 7:05 PM @snazztastic human beings 7:05 PM Hello people 7:06 PM Hope you liked jigging AND sawing 7:06 PM Im here to first, reveal the TIMES of everyone 1 7:06 PM Saying this was close would NOT be an overstatement, thats for sure 7:07 PM But it wouldnt be an understatement either. 7:07 PM With a difference by over an hour 7:07 PM 7:07 PM Jax takes the lead 7:07 PM Almost an hour 7:07 PM Oopsies 7:07 PM But... 7:08 PM The heart of the cards, right? 7:08 PM On Jax... 7:08 PM Cinnamon got their time DOUBLED. 7:08 PM Keira had their time TRIPLED 7:09 PM Tyler had his time HALVED 7:09 PM And LN's time doesn't count for the total. 3 7:09 PM On Ilana 7:10 PM Dreya had her time TRIPLED 1 7:10 PM Dar has their time DOUBLED 3 7:10 PM Pichu had their time HALVED 7:10 PM And Izzy B's time is NOT counted. 7:11 PM To those quick on the uptake... 7:11 PM By a difference of 1:47:54 to 2:58:35 7:12 PM @Jax wins their second immunity! 3 7:12 PM 7:13 PM Im letting Pilot do stuff Exported 50 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded',()=>{document.querySelectorAll('.chatlog__markdown-pre--multiline').forEach(e=>hljs.highlightBlock(e));}); document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded',()=>{document.querySelectorAll('.chatlog__sticker--media[data-source]').forEach(e=>{const anim=lottie.loadAnimation({container:e,renderer:'svg',loop:true,autoplay:true,path:e.getAttribute('data-source')});anim.addEventListener('data_failed',()=>e.innerHTML='[Sticker cannot be rendered]');});}); function scrollToMessage(event,id){const element=document.getElementById('chatlog__message-container-'+id);if(!element) return;event.preventDefault();element.classList.add('chatlog__message-container--highlighted');window.scrollTo({top:element.getBoundingClientRect().top-document.body.getBoundingClientRect().top-(window.innerHeight/2),behavior:'smooth'});window.setTimeout(()=>element.classList.remove('chatlog__message-container--highlighted'),2000);} function showSpoiler(event,element){if(!element) return;if(element.classList.contains('chatlog__attachment--hidden')){event.preventDefault();element.classList.remove('chatlog__attachment--hidden');} if(element.classList.contains('chatlog__markdown-spoiler--hidden')){event.preventDefault();element.classList.remove('chatlog__markdown-spoiler--hidden');}} Tagtreevivor S2: Planet Muski challenge Time Doesn't Count: Izzy B (edited) 1 Exported 1 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f15-immunity-challenge Armuski 10/13/2024 7:22 PM @Kaya @Lilly @All Updates 7:22 PM Hello!! 7:22 PM It's me 7:22 PM Your friendly 1 7:22 PM Swedish production member! 1 1 7:22 PM You see, in Sweden, we have this childhood game, that Ive decided to turn into a challenge for you all 7:23 PM # F15: Vi ska byta lag! 7:23 PM Roughly translated, that means 7:23 PM We're swapping teams 1 1 7:23 PM Now, this sounds 7:23 PM Like a swap 1 7:23 PM Ironically enough 7:24 PM Well too bad 7:24 PM Let me get the write up one sec 7:25 PM For this challenge, I'll need you all to divide into 2 TEAMS with 7 people. Theo will be on neither as he is immune! 7:25 PM Now the twist is 7:25 PM The teams are picked at random 7:25 PM @snazztastic human beings 7:25 PM STOP TALKING IN 1-1S 7:25 PM WERE SWAPPING 7:25 PM OR ALLIANCES 7:25 PM ALL CHATS 7:25 PM #mail 7:25 PM GO GO GO Austin 10/14/2024 7:00 PM Who’s ready for their first Austin challenge!! I’m I hope you all are enjoying your new tribes. Everything nice and cozy? Well now let’s get to our challenge! F15- Welcome to 1-on-1 Battleship with Trivia! This is just a fun game of Battleship…but with a twist! Isn’t that fun? You’ll take turns “firing at the other person’s board,” which is an 8x8 grid. When you call a shot (like “B4”), your opponent will say whether it’s a hit or a miss. If you get a hit, you shoot again! Then, your opponent takes their shot. That’s a round. Every 2 rounds, there will be a trivia question! The first person to answer correctly will get to choose between: • A random hint given by production (3 different types of hints, so your hints will vary). • Two extra shots on their next turn. The first person to sink all of their opponent’s ships wins the battle and gets a point for their tribe! The tribe with the most points after all the 7 1-on-1 battles wins immunity. Best of luck! Ping me with any questions. (edited) 7:03 PM Here is your board https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1F3OG85MFL0KAFsLV0fowX9y69LcaZaahtAbvTVz5XiA/edit F15 Immunity Challenge- Battleship Board- COPY ME!!!! 7:07 PM You will have a 1-on-1 setup with your opponent where prod and Theo will watch you 7:09 PM You will need to find a time with your opponent to do the challenge. It really needs to be run live. You have 24 hours to get it done! (edited) 7:12 PM Your matchups are: Pilot 10/14/2024 7:14 PM @snazztastic human beings Austin 10/14/2024 7:15 PM Send me a copy or photo of your boat placements in your subs Pilot 10/15/2024 2:17 PM Please have your board made and submitted before your start time! (edited) Austin 10/15/2024 7:05 PM Wow 7:06 PM My first challenge is officially over 7:06 PM @snazztastic human beings ready for results? 3 7:07 PM I’ve tallied all the results 7:07 PM I’m gonna say everyone did amazing 7:07 PM Now I’m gonna do something I hate 7:07 PM Long results!!! 7:07 PM 1 by 1 7:08 PM First up we have Derek vs Keira (edited) 7:09 PM Derek made quick work and sunk all 4 of Keira’s boats 7:09 PM Next up 7:09 PM Pichu vs Willow 7:09 PM This one um 7:10 PM This one had some timezone issues but 7:10 PM They got it done 7:10 PM Winning in a very close matchup is 7:10 PM .. 7:10 PM Pichu!!! 7:11 PM Ilana is up 2-0 7:11 PM Next up 7:11 PM We have is 7:11 PM Dar vs Brett 7:13 PM This one wasn’t as close 7:13 PM The winner won more trivia so that might’ve had to do with 7:13 PM Why 7:13 PM … 7:13 PM Brett won! 7:13 PM Jax scores their first point 7:13 PM Next up we have 7:13 PM LN vs Alba 7:14 PM Another close one with both of them only having 1 ship 7:14 PM But in the end 7:15 PM Alba! 7:15 PM Couldn’t come through! 7:15 PM LN gets a point! 7:15 PM We’re all tied up 7:15 PM 2-2 7:15 PM Next up is 7:15 PM Tyler vs Nate 7:16 PM This one come down to the wire 7:16 PM Coming down to a 1 ship each 7:17 PM But the person who was able to fire first was 7:17 PM It was 7:17 PM Tyler 7:17 PM And he hit! 7:17 PM Tyler puts Jax in the lead 7:17 PM 3-2 7:18 PM 2 matchups left 7:18 PM We have 7:18 PM Pigeon vs Izzy 7:18 PM Now 7:18 PM One of these people dominated the trivia 7:18 PM It was 7:18 PM Pigeon 7:18 PM But it didn’t matter because 7:19 PM Izzy sinks Pigeons ships first! 7:19 PM # WE’RE TIED 3-3 7:19 PM Comes down to 7:19 PM # Dreya vs Cinnamon 7:19 PM Our closest battle 7:20 PM Each person only had 1 boat life with only needing 1 more shot to sink 7:20 PM Who was able to get that shot first you ask? 7:20 PM Well…. 7:20 PM It 7:20 PM Was 7:20 PM Cinnamon 7:20 PM Who hits and sinks Dreyas last ship! 7:21 PM # which means Jax has won immunity 7:21 PM # 4-3 7:21 PM I’m sorry Ilana but we will be seeing you at our first tribal of the swap 7:21 PM But 7:21 PM Look on the bright side 7:21 PM Theo gets to join you after tribal! Here’s how it works, each of you will be split up into pairs, of your own choosing. Once your partners are chosen, you may not discuss anything related to the challenge with your partner or your will be DQ'd . Then, you will both complete a series of questions, about your partner or your relationship with your partner, so the better you've gotten to know your partnet the better! If you both answer the same answer to the question (or something reasonably close), you will receive a point. The tribe that gets the most points wins! 7:24 PM @Lilly You will be sitting one person out and @Kaya you will be sitting 3 people out (though they can still play if they want to, it just won't count) (edited) 7:24 PM And @13th-Dar must play 7:25 PM Please decide your partners ASAP, and there will be no warning about those DQs, 7:26 PM One last thing... 7:27 PM Both tribes will be attending tribal 7:27 PM This is still a tribal immunity challenge 7:28 PM But we will not be announcing the actual results until both tribes have completed a full tribal cycle, including reading the votes! 7:28 PM Then, only the player from the losing tribe will be eliminated 7:29 PM And just for fun, the player voted out of the winning tribe will be immune for the F15 cycle, regardless of what tribe wins or loses 7:29 PM exciting, right? 5 Pilot 10/12/2024 6:11 PM @snazztastic human beings , everyone has completed the challenge, so we're gonna open up tribal a little early seeing as we're not releasing challenge results rn anyways 6:11 PM You still may NOT discuss your answers with your partner 6:12 PM We will release the results of the challenge after the vote tmrw, till then, enjoy tribal! archive / f17-immunity-challenge Aunder 10/4/2024 11:42 AM F17: Word Detectives You all know how this works! For those who don't uhhhhh look it up :) Kidding kidding I'll explain if I must sigh For this challenge, you will be dividing into 4 pairs, each one consisting of one setter, and one "spiker" or solver The setter will be given a list of 10 words, and for each of them they'll have to come up with THREE CLUES that the solver will use one at a time to clue them into the word HOWEVER Each clue they come up with must be two words long, with other limitations (that may be specific to words) that make you have to get creative with your limited clues (edited) Aunder 10/9/2024 12:19 PM Once the setter has 30 clues, all approved by a host, the host will go to their matched solver and give them the list of the first 10 clues The solver will then guess a list of 10 words they think the setter was given! Every word they get right is 3 points If they get any wrong, they'll get the second clue for a chance at 2 points, then the last clue for 1 point if they get it. 3 wrongs and no points for a word With a maximum of 30 points, your tribe total will be added up amongst your three pairings for a total tribe result! Ping prod once your WHOLE TRIBE has decided their pairs. Kaya, since you have 1 extra member someone will be sitting out. Oh, and if we find out you are taking about the challenge with each other you will be penalized, and we will know! Don't cheat. Have fun! 12:24 PM Oh and an example would be: Space Clue 1: Off Earth Clue 2: Starry Sky Clue 3: Unoccupied Area My clues were bad but you get the idea! KawaiiQuack 10/9/2024 7:25 PM @snazztastic human beings You better not be able to talk in here Pilot 10/9/2024 7:27 PM Final deadline to submit the challenge is 10/10/2024 7:00 PM Winning tribe gets immunity, losing tribe goes to tribal! KawaiiQuack 10/9/2024 7:30 PM Kaya needs to sit someone out btw Aunder 10/9/2024 9:48 PM @snazztastic human beings I'll be home in about 2 hours and will send out any clues I can then, please be patient with ne work is on my ass rn 9:54 PM If I get a direct ping between now and then -1 million points for the challenge btw Pilot 10/10/2024 7:00 PM Results shortly! 7:05 PM Alright @snazztastic human beings Challenge result time! 1 7:05 PM We're gonna go pair by pair 7:06 PM First, Willow and Pigeon 7:06 PM who got a score of... 7:06 PM 27 for Kaya 2 7:07 PM Next, Derek and Izzy B 7:07 PM who who got a score of... 21 for Lilly 7:07 PM Keira/Cinnamon 7:07 PM With a score of... 7:08 PM 17 for Kaya 7:08 PM Tyler/Brett 7:08 PM with a score of 7:08 PM 23 for Lilly 7:08 PM Which ties us up! 44 to 44 7:08 PM close challenge 7:09 PM Night and LN are next 7:09 PM with a score of 7:09 PM 17 for Kaya 7:09 PM GScrub and Theo 7:09 PM with a score of 7:09 PM 19 for Lilly! 7:10 PM Meaning Lilly now leads 63-61 7:10 PM down to our last pair per tribe 7:10 PM Alba and Pichu 7:10 PM scored 7:11 PM 26 for Kaya! 7:11 PM Making the score 87 to 63 7:12 PM Lilly needs 25 points to win from Nate/Dreya 7:12 PM Could they do it? 7:12 PM They could not 1 7:13 PM with only 12 points, the final score is 87 to 75 1 7:13 PM Meaning @Lilly is going back to tribal council! 1 1 7:14 PM Words + final score Pilot Lilly needs 25 points to win from Nate/Dreya Pilot 10/10/2024 7:14 PM Also, Kaya won in the case of the tiebreaker, so Lilly needed 25 points Exported 43 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

7:17 PM challenge time? 7:17 PM so welcome to my challenge 7:17 PM F19: Word Search!!! 7:18 PM It is as simple as it sounds 7:19 PM When you input the command ? f19-search, You will be given a word search. It's in a google drawing, but you can save the image, make a copy, utilize photo editing software, whatever you want. 7:19 PM You will have one hour to complete it. To submit, simply post a screenshot of your word search, with it being clear what you found so it is easier for me to grade. 7:21 PM If you go over an hour, your score is invalid. If nobody solves it completely, the person with the most words found wins. If that is a tie, the winner will be whoever submitted faster. 7:21 PM Now you might be asking yourself 7:21 PM This sounds an awful lot like an individual immunity challenge 7:21 PM ... 7:21 PM That's because it is! 7:22 PM Both tribes will be going to tribal council and voting somebody out, with the winner from each tribe earning immunity. 7:22 PM One last thing What are the words you are searching for, you might ask 7:22 PM well 7:23 PM your word bank is in #cast-list so good luck and have fun, and ping me with any questions! Because I might have forgotten something 7:23 PM I should mention in case it wasn't clear 7:23 PM Your time for the search starts when you input the command (edited) KawaiiQuack your word bank is in #cast-list so good luck and have fun, and ping me with any questions! Because I might have forgotten something KawaiiQuack 10/7/2024 7:24 PM Emphasizing this too, you wanna make sure you know what you're looking for! 7:26 PM Oh I did forget something 7:26 PM Twenty words You are looking for twenty words Pilot 10/7/2024 7:38 PM Deadline to finish the challenge is 10/8/2024 7:00 PM KawaiiQuack 10/8/2024 7:01 PM Results soon 2 KawaiiQuack 10/8/2024 7:08 PM @All Updates @snazztastic human beings hello! 7:08 PM Who is ready for some results 3 1 2 7:09 PM Mixed reactions I see 7:09 PM Let's get into it 7:09 PM Starting with a DNF 7:09 PM @Brad 7:10 PM Oh yeah I will be going through all 19 of you as a group 4 7:10 PM For fun 7:10 PM Anyways 7:10 PM With 2/20 words found 4 7:10 PM @17th-GScrub 1 7:10 PM With 15/20 words found... 7:11 PM @5th-Cinnamon 7:11 PM The rest of you got all 20! 7:11 PM Good job 7:11 PM We had a wide variety of times though 7:12 PM With 58:45, @6th-IzzyB does not win @9th-Dreya was barely faster, with a time of 57:14 1 7:12 PM Ten minute jump to @14th-Theo , with a time of 47:41 7:13 PM @2nd-Pigeon and @10th-Pichu are next, with 44:14 and 43:16 respectively 7:13 PM @3rd-Willow had a time of 42:49 7:13 PM And @19th-Etay got a flat 40 7:14 PM @4th-Tyler is next with 38:16, followed by @11th-Nate with 37:19 7:15 PM @Alba had a time of 36:17 @13th-Dar had 35:06 And @Keira had 33:35 7:15 PM Which leaves us with our top 4! 7:16 PM Two per tribe 7:16 PM How fun 7:16 PM Let's start with Kaya 7:16 PM LN and Night This was not close 7:16 PM @1st-LN had a time of exactly 30 minutes 7:17 PM And @16th-Night had exactly half of that, with 15 minutes flat 7:17 PM Meaning Night wins immunity for the Kaya tribe! 7:18 PM And he was also the fastest person overall 7:18 PM Which means he wins a reward That being his tribe will vote someone out in 18th, Lilly will be 19th 7:18 PM What an epic reward 7:18 PM Ok next 7:18 PM Brett and Derek 7:18 PM This was much closer 7:19 PM Two minutes apart! 7:19 PM With a time of 20:41... 7:19 PM @7th-Brett does NOT win immunity @derek ⟡ wins with a time of 18:48! 7:19 PM Congratulations 7:20 PM Tribals will be set up Good luck all! (edited) 7:04 PM Kaya scored... 7:04 PM 38 (edited) 7:04 PM Lilly scored... 7:04 PM 36 7:05 PM Soooo 120 Kaya, 98 Lilly 7:05 PM For Teamwork 7:05 PM Kaya scored... 7:06 PM 46 7:06 PM And Lilly scored 7:06 PM 21 2 7:06 PM 166 Kaya, 119 Lilly 1 7:06 PM On the web 7:06 PM Kaya scored... 7:07 PM 44 (edited) 7:07 PM Lilly scored... 39 1 7:08 PM That's 210 Kaya, 158 Lilly 7:08 PM With Lilly behind by 52 points, they would need to get almost all the remaining points to win 7:09 PM On interstellar, Kaya scored 7:09 PM 12 7:09 PM For a total of 222 7:09 PM And Lilly scored 7:09 PM 23 7:09 PM For a total score of 181 7:09 PM Which means @Kaya Congratulations , you're immune 7:10 PM And @Lilly you'll be voting the first person out of this game Exported 60 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f5-immunity-challenge Dicy 11/2/2024 2:49 PM Dicy Challenge part 2, Welcome to your Final 5 Immunity challenge. # F5: Empty Space (edited) Dicy 11/5/2024 4:09 PM For todays Challenge I have created a bit of a puzzle chain for you to solve! There will be three different puzzle types that you will be solving, all that involve filling in the empty space. Once the puzzle is completed you will then use your completed to puzzle to find a hidden code within the puzzle, you will enter those hidden codes into their marked locations on the cover page to reveal the season logo. How you find these "hidden codes" will be clearly marked on each of the puzzles respect google sheet tab. you will know you have the Hidden code correct as a cell will change to a piece of the season logo, if it doesn't you are wrong. I will go ahead and tell you the three puzzle types that will be included in this challenge to allow for practice on your own before running the challenge. The three puzzles are: Framework Puzzle : a grid resembling a crossword, but instead of clues, you're provided with a list of scrambled words. Your goal is to fit these words into the grid, unscrambling them as you go. Numbrix Puzzle : consists of a grid of numbers. The goal is to fill in the grid with numbers in sequential order, starting from 1 and ending at the highest number given. Each number must be adjacent to the previous or next number in sequence, either horizontally or vertically. Some Numbers will be given to start the puzzle to guide your solve. Drop Quote Puzzle : a grid of squares and a set of given letters which “drop” into the grid. When the puzzle is solved, You will have a phrase of some kind. Within the grid, black boxes represent the spaces between words. some words may be broken between lines, starting at the end of one line and continuing to the beginning of the next line — words only end at black boxes or the end of the puzzle. The given letters at the bottom of a drop quote puzzle are organized by the column they “drop” into, and are given in alphabetical order. (edited) 4:13 PM The rules for the challenge are very straight forward: Enter the command !F5-Empty-Space (This will give you the google sheets page, MAKE A COPY) Solve each tabs Puzzle and send a screenshot for proof Solve the three Hidden Codes and enter them on the cover page to reveal the logo then send a screenshot of the completed cover page! Challenge will be due at Wednesday, November 6, 2024 8:00 PM if you have any questions please ping me in your submissions. KawaiiQuack 11/5/2024 7:23 PM @snazztastic human beings welcome to the mandatory Dicy challenge Dicy 11/6/2024 8:01 PM @Kireina @All Updates I have some results 8:01 PM Ill make them quick tonight 8:01 PM in 5th place 8:01 PM Cinnanmon with a DNF 8:02 PM next in 4th place with a time of 1:09:39 1 8:02 PM Pigeon 8:02 PM but not much quicker in 3rd place 8:03 PM with a time of 1:04:28 1 8:03 PM LN 8:03 PM now our top two were both a bit faster 8:03 PM both doing well under an hour 8:03 PM but who wins tyler or willow 8:04 PM with a time of..... 21:26 8:04 PM @3rd-Willow has won induvial immunity over Tylers 34:11 Exported 18 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f6-immunity-challenge Cwiski 10/11/2024 7:22 AM F6: Rankings and Queens Hey y’all! Who’s ready for their second Cwis challenge of the season? So for this challenge, I drew inspiration from a jackbox game that some of y’all might be familiar with, it’s called Quixort . Here’s how todays challenge will work: Upon entering the command, you will be given 3 questions/prompts about the season, as well as their answers. Your goal for each prompt is to rank the answers in the correct order. An example prompt would look like this: Order the planets in our solar system from closest to furthest from the sun: Earth, Jupiter, Mars, Mercury, Neptune, Saturn, Uranus, Venus For simplicity sake and using the example above, I ask that you input your answers as such: Prompt 1: 1. Mercury 2. Venus 3. Earth 4. Mars 5. Jupiter 6. Saturn 7. Uranus 8. Neptune With a potential total of 30 points, you will earn one point per correct placement, and the castaway with the most prompts correctly placed will win individual immunity (with tiebreaker coming down to who took less time to submit from entering the command) Should there be any ties while ranking, the placement of the items within the tie do not matter. Hope that’s simple enough! Keep in mind that when you enter the command you will be given all 3 prompts at once, so plan your time accordingly. The command is "?f6-rank" Good luck and have fun (edited) Cwiski 11/3/2024 7:43 PM @Kireina Another Cwis Challenge! Go nuts and ping if you have any questions Cwiski 11/3/2024 8:01 PM Also no discussion of the challenge please and thank you! Cwiski 11/4/2024 6:27 PM @Kireina @All Updates who wants some early results?? 6:27 PM I do because I’m at the gym! 6:28 PM A small note: I made an Oopsie and didn’t establish that only the losing tribe attended f12 tribal, so there are different answers allowed for prompt 1, but it didn’t affect the overall outcome 6:28 PM ANYWAYS LETS DO IT 6:28 PM in 6th place is @3rd-Willow with 10/30 6:29 PM In 5th is @5th-Cinnamon with 22/30 6:29 PM In 4th is @2nd-Pigeon with 25/30 6:29 PM In 3rd is @1st-LN with 29/30 6:30 PM Meaning our two remaining players, @6th-IzzyB and @4th-Tyler both scored a 30/30! So it comes down to time 6:30 PM Izzy got a time of 23:48 6:30 PM Was Tyler able to beat that? 6:30 PM They… 6:30 PM . 6:30 PM . 6:30 PM . 6:31 PM Did! With a time of 19:26, @4th-Tyler wins immunity! 6:31 PM Congrats Tyler, if anyone has questions about your scores feel free to ask and I will get back to you after the gym Exported 20 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f7-immunity-challenge Austin 11/1/2024 1:38 PM Woooo Austin challenge number 2!!! I know you guys missed me and my overly complicated way of things! 1:38 PM Today we have 1:38 PM # Gauntlet Games! 1:38 PM Here’s how it will work: In this challenge, you’ll face a series of rounds designed to test different skills. Each of you will complete all four parts of the challenge, but only those who survive each round will have their scores counted for the following rounds. If you’re eliminated in a round, your scores in later rounds won’t matter. You won’t know until the end at results! The details of each challenge will be revealed as you begin each one. So, stay sharp and give each round your best effort—your immunity is on the line! Here’s an outline: • Round 1: The two lowest scores/times will be eliminated, leaving 5 players eligible for the next round. • Round 2: The two lowest scores/times will be eliminated from the 5 eligible, leaving 3 players eligible for the next round. • Final Round: The player with the best time/score, between the 3 eligible people, will win individual immunity! Everyone will complete all rounds, but only the remaining eligible players’ scores will be considered each time. Best of luck—let’s see who can adapt and conquer! First command- ?challenge-1 Second Command- ?challenge-2 Their Command- ?challenge-3 Finish each challenge before starting the next! Also you will be timed from the time you put in the command so be ready! Please ping me with questions I know this can be confusing KawaiiQuack 11/1/2024 7:29 PM @snazztastic human beings just in case you did not see it Austin 11/2/2024 7:07 PM Wooo 7:07 PM Who’s ready for results!!! 1 7:08 PM Okay first off we have the tower Hanoi race 7:08 PM Everyone loved this one right (: 1 7:09 PM Well first off we have willow 7:09 PM Who completed it in 88 moves!!! 7:10 PM Next we have 7:10 PM LN, Brett and Tyler… 7:10 PM All with perfect scores of 63! 7:11 PM Next up is Cinnamon 7:11 PM Who sadly had a DNF 7:11 PM So we have our first eliminated 7:11 PM Next up is Pigeon 7:12 PM Needs to beat Willows score of 88 to survive 7:12 PM And they did!!! 7:12 PM With 67 7:12 PM Now it’s down to Willow vs Izzy 7:12 PM Izzy needs to beat 88 7:12 PM She did 7:12 PM NOT 7:13 PM With a score of 92 7:13 PM So our next 5 move onto WiKi race 7:13 PM Let’s start off with 7:13 PM Tyler 7:13 PM Who got a respectable time of 7:14 PM 17 seconds!!!! 2 7:14 PM Yes that’s right 7:14 PM Next up is Willow 7:15 PM Barely surviving last round 7:15 PM Got a time of 2:10 7:15 PM Doesn’t beat Tyler 7:15 PM How surprising 7:15 PM Next we have 7:15 PM LN 7:16 PM Who got a time of 5 minutes 7:16 PM Now we have pigeon 7:17 PM Who got a time of 1:01 7:17 PM Which means LN has been eliminated 7:17 PM Now it’s down to Brett… and Willow once again 7:17 PM Brett needs to beat a time of 2:10 7:17 PM He got 7:18 PM 3:11 7:18 PM Which means he’s eliminated and Willow moves onto the final round!!! 7:18 PM Okay now for those emojis 7:19 PM You loved it 7:19 PM Starting off with Willow who got a time of 7:37 7:19 PM Now we have Tyler 7:19 PM Who 7:19 PM Blew it out of the water with 4:40 7:20 PM Now we’re down to Tyler vs Pigeon 7:20 PM Pigeon score was 1 off from Tyler 7:20 PM Wow 7:20 PM Was it 1 above or 1 below 7:20 PM It… 7:20 PM Was… 7:21 PM 4:39 1 7:21 PM Congratulations Pigeon!!!! archive / f8-immunity-challenge Cwiski 10/8/2024 7:14 PM F8: Time to Game! Guys I'm going to keep this short, sweet, and to the point: I love to game! Whether it be singleplayer or with friends, I am a gamer at heart! With this, I figured I would share my love of gaming with all of you, and have you compete in a gaming challenge! Isn't that so fun??? Last season I ran a speedrunning challenge, and this season I thought I’d do the opposite. Let’s take our time here, shall we? The challenge is simple: when you're ready you will enter the command "?f8-gamer" into your submissions channel. Upon entering the command, you will receive the link to the game you will be playing. The moment the command is entered, you will have 1 hour to achieve the highest score possbile you can in said game. The player who records the highest score will be the winner of individual immunity, with tiebreakers coming down to who submitted their score fastest within that hour timeframe. You may submit as many scores as you'd like within the hour, and we will be taking the highest score you submit! It's as simple as that! Good luck gamers (edited) Cwiski 10/29/2024 7:21 PM @Kireina @All Updates cwis challenge! go nuts Cwiski 10/29/2024 7:33 PM Reminder not to discuss the challenge/selected game with anyone Cwiski 10/30/2024 2:32 PM @Kireina sorry for the ping As per request, will be extending the challenge a bit. The latest you can run the command is 8:00pm EST, meaning results will come out around 9:00pm EST Cwiski 10/30/2024 9:00 PM @Kireina @All Updates and that’s time! Let’s move through this quickly so I can watch the Yankee game 9:01 PM In 8th place is Cinnamon with 4 In 7th place is Alba with 25 In 6th place is IzzyB with 35 9:01 PM In 5th is pigeon with 53 9:02 PM Just ahead with 59 is Tyler in 4th 9:02 PM Down to the top 3! Wow! So crazy! 9:02 PM Getting the bronze medal is LN with a score of 64 9:03 PM Leaving us with @Brett and @Willow vying for 1st and 2nd 9:03 PM Willow netted a score of 71 but was that enough to beat Brett? 9:03 PM It 9:03 PM . 9:03 PM . 9:03 PM . 9:04 PM Was not! As Brett earns immunity with a solid score of 96. Congrats @Brett ! To tribal with the rest of you thank you for playing my funky game Exported 17 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f9-immunity-challenge Armuski 10/27/2024 6:34 PM F9: Beyond the stars! For this challenge, you'll be doing a few mini challenges! You can pick as many as you want, ranging in difficulty from 1-12. For every challenge you do, you get an amount of points, that being the amount that was stated on the difficulty. So if you were to do challenge nine, you would get nine points by completing it! If you were to FAIL a challenge however, you lose half of the points of that challenge AND any challenges you do afterwards will not count for your total. Let's say Aunder is doing their thing. They complete challenge one, three, and five. They sit at a pretty nine points. They feel cocky and go for challenge 12, but lose. That means they lose six points, and their challenge ends with him getting 3 points total. You can do them in any order you'd like, so feel free to start wherever you'd like! I heavily encourage having some sort of editing software on hand. The command for the challenges are "?planet-x" where x is the difficulty.
